Date: Sat 6 Dec 2014
From: Ignace Surmont MD <Ignace.Surmont@azsintjan.be> [edited]


Trichinellosis in Belgium from imported wild boar
-------------------------------------------------
At least 9 persons in the province of Limburg [Belgium] are suffering from an infection due to _Trichinella spiralis_ after eating boar meat -- probably imported from Spain -- in the previous month [November-December 2014]. Other cases from other provinces will probably be detected in the near future since Belgian authorities warned the public in a radio message.

Trichinosis is a virtually unknown disease in Belgium since it disappeared some 100 years ago.

--
Ignace Surmont MD
Sint Jan Hospital Bruges-Oostende
Infection Prevention/Microbiology
Ruddershove 10
