Belgium
<Ignace.Surmont@azsintjan.be>

[_Trichinella_ spp. can survive in dried and cured meat, and infections for instance by salami manufactured in one country and consumed in another country is not unusual. - Mod.EP

Information on the origin of the implicated source of tainted boar meat would be greatly appreciated (where in Spain, was this a 'commercial' product or artesanal?). - Mod.MPP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3015631,27639.]
